      <p>
        <s>The given passage of the novel <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="title">The Hate U Give</ref>, written by <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="author">Angie Thomas</ref>, is the beginning of the scene when <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr</ref> finally manages to speak openly and in <choice><orig>publicly</orig><reg>public</reg></choice> about <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Khalil's</ref> death.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>The passage starts with <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr</ref>, <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">DeVante</ref>, <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Seven</ref> and <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Chris</ref> arriving at the place where <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Khalil</ref> was shot.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>There is a crowd protesting but <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr</ref> just relives the moment when <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Khalil</ref> was shot.</s>
        <s>They see <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr's</ref> attorney who sees and approaches them.</s>
        <s>They talk about the other protests and that <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr</ref> wants to speak up.</s>
        <s>The scene ends <choice><orig>whith</orig><reg>with</reg></choice> <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Ms. Ofrah</ref> asking <ref target="a11gk3_1" type="character">Starr</ref> whether she wants to fight the system.</s>
      </p>
